    <div class="reason-grid">
      <div class="reason-card"><div class="service-card-header"><div class="reason-icon">🩻</div><h4>Peritoneal Mesothelioma</h4></div><p>CRS+HIPEC is the standard of care. Best long-term outcomes of all peritoneal surface malignancies.</p></div>
      <div class="reason-card"><div class="service-card-header"><div class="reason-icon">🩻</div><h4>Pseudomyxoma Peritonei (PMP)</h4></div><p>Appendix-origin. Sugarbaker technique. Potentially curative with complete cytoreduction.</p></div>
      <div class="reason-card"><div class="service-card-header"><div class="reason-icon">🩻</div><h4>Colorectal Peritoneal Metastases</h4></div><p>Selected cases with PCI below 20. PRODIGE 7 trial evidence base.</p></div>
      <div class="reason-card"><div class="service-card-header"><div class="reason-icon">🩻</div><h4>Ovarian Cancer</h4></div><p>Interval debulking + HIPEC. OVHIPEC trial (NEJM 2018) showed survival improvement.</p></div>
      <div class="reason-card"><div class="service-card-header"><div class="reason-icon">🩻</div><h4>Gastric Peritoneal Metastases</h4></div><p>Carefully selected cases. Tumor Board evaluation required. PCI and disease biology determine candidacy.</p></div>
      <div class="reason-card"><div class="service-card-header"><div class="reason-icon">⚖️</div><h4>Not Suitable For</h4></div><p>PCI above 20, poor performance status, significant comorbidities, distant metastases beyond peritoneum. I tell patients honestly when they are not candidates.</p></div>
